snippet.textDisplay:
There is type of this called "Bone Soup". It is all the same way that you make chicken soup, no? Meat, vegetables, and water. In Bone soup you foolow the same recipe, but add "root vegetables", i.e. Whole garlic head/cloves, leaks, potato cubes, onion halves, dill root, parley root, coriander root. You get same "brote" but wit lots of vegetables and spices... and you DON'T REMOVE the bone marrow.
Serve it steaming hot in big bowls of soup and vegetables and enjoy your winter.
